<subSubSection id="1B14D43C2C878049F7115B096F0E2C8C" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" type="conservation status">
<paragraph id="32AE15C83A0505D8F1F6EBCF42AE6AC1" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">Conservation status.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="189340D2C89C42CB0490F18078D4EAF4" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">
During separate cliff rappels five subpopulations ranging in size from 1 to 30-50 plants were observed on vertical cliff faces, for a total of 113 individuals observed (
<bibRefCitation id="953D97945D28B08D2E48F455DE61F88E" author="Perlman, S" journalOrPublisher="National Tropical Botanical Garden, Botanical Survey Report (unpublished)" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" refId="B13" refString="Perlman, S, Wood, KR, 1994. Anderson (sic) Air Force Base rare plant survey of their limestone Forests and cliffs, Northern Marianas Islands, Guam. Prepared for the U.S. Fish and Wildlife Service. National Tropical Botanical Garden, Botanical Survey Report (unpublished)" title="Anderson (sic) Air Force Base rare plant survey of their limestone Forests and cliffs, Northern Marianas Islands, Guam. Prepared for the U. S. Fish and Wildlife Service." year="1994">Perlman and Wood 1994</bibRefCitation>
) (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="EEAB6679743856F51CCAD5AF7A25D9DD" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Distribution map showing five known localities for Pogostemon guamensis on NE part of Guam." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.169.58107.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/482074" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">5</figureCitation>
). Based on the IUCN categories and criteria this species is assigned a preliminary Red List status of Critically Endangered (CR) based on its AOO of &lt;10 km² (i.e., 4 km²) and its EOO of &lt;100 km² (i.e., 4 km²), and it has only one known location, with continuing decline in both AOO and EOO inferred.
</paragraph>
<caption id="C6E5E91D0F407013CF0251278E593228" doi="10.3897/phytokeys.169.58107.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/482074" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" start="Figure 5" startId="F5">
<paragraph id="9D87B2C9CF5DF16F491983F6EA4E5682" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">
<emphasis id="DD617E58A9D9A0EA755CF9ECD995C7C5" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="61">Figure 5.</emphasis>
Distribution map showing five known localities for 
<taxonomicName id="C4BD9348BC61D48E78300A9A9A9CAA9E" authorityName="Lorence &amp; W. L. Wagner" authorityYear="2020" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lamiaceae" genus="Pogostemon" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Pogostemon guamensis" order="Lamiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="61" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="guamensis">
